Codebook: Sports Car Prices Dataset

Dataset Source:
Rattanaporn, K. (n.d.). Sports Car Prices Dataset [Data set]. Kaggle.
https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/rkiattisak/sports-car-prices-dataset

Variable Descriptions:

Car Make/car_make
- The manufacturer or brand of the vehicle (e.g., Ferrari, Porsche, Lamborghini).

Car model/car_model
- The model of the sports car, representing the specific version or variant of car produced by the manufacturer (e.g., 911, Huracan, 488 GTB, M8).

Year/year
- The model year of the car.

Engine Size (L)/engine_size_l
- Original engine size variable from the dataset.
- Represents engine displacement is liters for gasoline vehicles.
- May contain non-numeric values (e.g., "Electric") for electric or hybrid cars.

Horsepower
- The power output of the car's engine, measured in horsepower (hp).

Torque/torque_lb_ft
- Engine torque, measured in pound-feet (lb-ft).

0-60 MPH Time (seconds)/x0_60_mph_time_seconds
- Time required for the car to accelerate from 0 to 60 mph
- Measured in seconds

Price (in USD)/price_in_usd
- The price of sports car in US dollars

Notes on cleaning:
- Duplicate rows based on make, model, and year were removed
- Text-based numeric fields were converted into numeric form for analysis
- engine_size_num was created from engine_size_l
- Missing values in engine_size_num were imputed in the modeling recipe